params.amountToBorrow: amount of WETH to borrow. Due to rounding, true borrow amount might be slightly less.
params.proof: merkle proof that the user is whitelisted.

flashDeleverageWethAndSwap(uint256,uint2.details: Uniswap flashloans do incur a fee.

params.debtToRemove: The desired amount of debt to remove.
params.maxCollateralToRemove: The max amount of collateral willing to sell to repay `debtToRemove` debt.

params.maxResultingDebt: in WETH terms. While it is unlikely that the exchange rate changes from when a transaction is submitted versus when it is executed, it is still possible so we want to allow for a bound here, even though it doesn't pose the same level of threat as slippage.

in WETH terms. While it is unlikely that the exchange rate changes from when a transaction is submitted versus when it is executed, it is still possible so we want to allow for a bound here, even though it doesn't pose the same level of threat as slippage.

params.maxResultingAdditionalDebt: in WETH terms. This value also allows the user to control slippage of the swap.

receiveFlashLoan(address[],uint256[],uin.details: This function is intended to never be called directly. It should only be called by the Balancer VAULT during a flashloan initiated by this contract. This callback logic only handles the creation of leverage positions by minting. Since not all tokens have withdrawable liquidity via the LST protocol directly, deleverage through the protocol will need to be implemented in the inheriting contract.

params.userData: arbitrary data passed from initiator of flash loan

uniswapV3FlashCallback(uint256,uint256,b.details: In the implementation you must repay the pool the tokens sent by flash plus the computed fee amounts. The caller of this method must be checked to be a UniswapV3Pool deployed by the canonical UniswapV3Factory.

params.data: Any data passed through by the caller via the IUniswapV3PoolActions#flash call
params.fee0: The fee amount in tokenInBalancer due to the pool by the end of the flash
params.fee1: The fee amount in tokenOutBalancer due to the pool by the end of the flash

flashLeverageCollateral(uint256,uint256,.notice: Code assumes Balancer flashloans remain free

flashLeverageWeth(uint256,uint256,uint25.notice: Code assumes Balancer flashloans remain free

flashLeverageWethAndSwap(uint256,uint256.notice: Uniswap flashloans do incur a fee.

receiveFlashLoan(address[],uint256[],uin.notice: Code assumes Balancer flashloans remain free.

uniswapV3FlashCallback(uint256,uint256,b.notice: Called to `msg.sender` after transferring to the recipient from IUniswapV3Pool#flash.
